It took 2.5 hours to get this done, but the calcium reactor is now clean and loaded. Should be good for the majority of 2023. The flow going into the reactor was a problem, and after everything was cleaned, I discovered the blue 1/4” tubing was packed with sediment, preventing water movement. I replaced the tubing with a new piece and it’s running right. That tubing was never a consideration in all these years, who knows how long this was going on.
